1 whic h may also be cited as "BIND – Technology Fund". The fund shall
2 be a continuing fund, not subject to fiscal year limitations, and
3 shall consist of all monies directed for deposit to the fund by law.
4 All monies accruing to the credit of said fund are hereby
5 appropriated and may be budgeted and expended by the Oklahoma
6 Military Department for the purpose established in Subsection B of
7 this section. Expenditures from said fund shall be made upon
8 warrants issued by the State Treasurer against claims filed as
9 prescribed by law with the Director of the Office of Management and
10 Enterprise Services for approval and payment.
11 B. There is hereby established within the Oklahoma Military
12 Department the "Base Infrastructure Needs and Development –
13 Technology Program", which may also be cited as the "BIND –
14 Technology Program". The Department shall utilize funds from the
15 BIND – Technology Fund created in Subsection A of this section,
16 alone or in combination with other available funding, to make
17 infrastructure investments, including, but not limited to, the
18 purchase of licenses and software associated with military
19 simulation training, that will either:
20 1. Decrease the likelihood of military base and other military
21 infrastructure closures in this state, or
22 2. Increase the likelihood of military base and other military
23 infrastructure expansions in this state.
24 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
